---
description: Enforce nuqs grouped filters with short object and short keys
alwaysApply: true
---

# URL Search/Filter Standards

- For search/filter state in URL, always use `useQueryStates` from `nuqs`.
- Group filter params into one short object name (prefer `f`).
- Use short keys inside filter object to keep querystring compact:
  - `q` = keyword
  - `s` = status
  - `p` = price
  - `o` = sort order
  - `c` = category
- Keep parser definitions colocated in one `useQueryStates` call.
- Use the same short keys in `queryKey` and `URLSearchParams` mapping.

## Required Pattern

```tsx
import { parseAsString, useQueryStates } from 'nuqs';

const [f, setF] = useQueryStates({
  q: parseAsString.withDefault(''),
  s: parseAsString.withDefault(''),
  p: parseAsString.withDefault(''),
  o: parseAsString.withDefault('popular'),
});

const query = useQuery({
  queryKey: ['orders', f.s, f.q, f.o],
  queryFn: async () => {
    const params = new URLSearchParams();
    if (f.s) params.set('status', f.s);
    if (f.q) params.set('q', f.q.trim());
    const res = await fetch(`/api/orders?${params.toString()}`);
    return res.json();
  },
});
```

## Avoid

```tsx
const [filters, setFilters] = useQueryStates({
  status: parseAsString.withDefault(''),
  searchKeyword: parseAsString.withDefault(''),
  sortOrder: parseAsString.withDefault('popular'),
});
```
